class Board[source]

Board(url)

Represents a rendered board with particular dark and light colors. There are no pieces on the board.

so far assumes the board is oriented towards the white player

PieceSet and PieceSets

{% raw %}

class PieceSet[source]

PieceSet(dir)

Represents the 12 individual pieces comprising a chess set. This includes a rook, knight, bishop, queen, king, and pawn for both black and white pieces.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

class FEN[source]

FEN(fen) :: Board

represents a fen string with convenience methods to find the piece on each square

test_eq(FEN(s).h8, 'r')
test_eq(FEN(s).e3, '_')
test_eq(FEN(s).e1, 'K')

GameBoard

{% raw %}

class GameBoard[source]

GameBoard()

Represents a combination of a Board, PieceSet, and optionally a FEN to create the position. If no fen is provided, the GameBoard will be in the starting position

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
board = choice(boards)
board.reset()
piece = choice(pieces)
gb = GameBoard(board, piece, FEN(s)); gb
{% endraw %}
